        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 13 at 4:16PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 416 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Goshen, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Troy, Goshen, Linwood, Troy Municipal Airport, Troy University,
Sandfield, Orion, Mossy Grove, and Henderson.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
